00:43:53.047 --> 00:43:59.320 line:90% position:50% align:center
The voice of the stranger
Leads only to danger.

00:43:59.320 --> 00:44:09.263 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s Jesus’ words
I hear and obey.

00:44:10.531 --> 00:44:16.870 line:90% position:50% align:center
To whom
could I go away?

00:44:16.870 --> 00:44:32.853 line:90% position:50% align:center
Never, never ever will I stray.

00:44:34.154 --> 00:44:37.725 line:90% position:50% align:center
Certainly, that’s how we all feel.

00:44:37.725 --> 00:44:40.060 line:90% position:50% align:center
Never do we want to stray

00:44:40.060 --> 00:44:43.130 line:90% position:50% align:center
from “the great shepherd,” Jesus Christ,

00:44:43.130 --> 00:44:48.068 line:90% position:50% align:center
as he leads us through the end
of this troubled system of things.

00:44:48.068 --> 00:44:50.437 line:90% position:50% align:center
May this song encourage us

00:44:50.437 --> 00:44:53.941 line:90% position:50% align:center
to stick close to Jehovah’s organization

00:44:53.941 --> 00:44:56.844 line:90% position:50% align:center
no matter what befalls us.

00:44:58.145 --> 00:45:03.117 line:90% position:50% align:center
For imperfect humans,
unity rarely comes easily.

00:45:03.117 --> 00:45:05.786 line:90% position:50% align:center
In our following video, please note

00:45:05.786 --> 00:45:09.056 line:90% position:50% align:center
how the Governing Body has always worked

00:45:09.056 --> 00:45:11.492 line:90% position:50% align:center
to maintain unity

00:45:11.492 --> 00:45:15.028 line:90% position:50% align:center
in behalf of the worldwide brotherhood.

00:45:21.869 --> 00:45:24.605 line:90% position:50% align:center
You know I’ve had an illness,

00:45:24.605 --> 00:45:28.075 line:90% position:50% align:center
but I’m getting along all right.

00:45:30.511 --> 00:45:35.149 line:90% position:50% align:center
There’s a little tumor here in the brain,

00:45:35.149 --> 00:45:37.317 line:90% position:50% align:center
which the doctors are treating.

00:45:38.952 --> 00:45:43.257 line:90% position:50% align:center
And whatever comes, one way or the other,

00:45:45.993 --> 00:45:50.397 line:90% position:50% align:center
well, it has been wonderful
to work with you all these years,

00:45:51.799 --> 00:45:54.768 line:90% position:50% align:center
and I enjoyed it tremendously.

00:45:54.768 --> 00:45:56.970 line:90% position:50% align:center
And I’m very grateful to Jehovah

00:45:56.970 --> 00:46:00.274 line:90% position:50% align:center
I could come to this meeting

00:46:00.274 --> 00:46:01.775 line:90% position:50% align:center
and be with you.

00:46:16.190 --> 00:46:18.025 line:90% position:50% align:center
Like C. T. Russell before him,

00:46:18.025 --> 00:46:20.461 line:90% position:50% align:center
Brother Knorr had an exceptional gift

00:46:20.461 --> 00:46:22.463 line:90% position:50% align:center
for organizing the Kingdom work.

00:46:23.530 --> 00:46:25.999 line:90% position:50% align:center
That set the stage for the amazing growth

00:46:25.999 --> 00:46:28.869 line:90% position:50% align:center
that the organization experienced
during the closing decades

00:46:28.869 --> 00:46:31.472 line:90% position:50% align:center
of the 20th century.

00:46:31.472 --> 00:46:35.843 line:10% position:50% align:center
Nathan Knorr died on June 8, 1977.

00:46:35.843 --> 00:46:38.178 line:10% position:50% align:center
Note what Brother Albert Schroeder,

00:46:38.178 --> 00:46:39.880 line:10% position:50% align:center
a fellow member of the Governing Body,

00:46:39.880 --> 00:46:41.682 line:10% position:50% align:center
wrote about him:

00:46:41.682 --> 00:46:44.384 line:90% position:50% align:center
“As the Society’s principal administrator,

00:46:44.384 --> 00:46:46.954 line:90% position:50% align:center
“there have come to be over 90 branches.

00:46:46.954 --> 00:46:48.956 line:90% position:50% align:center
“Brother Knorr has proved to be

00:46:48.956 --> 00:46:51.325 line:90% position:50% align:center
“the right theocratic entrepreneur

00:46:51.325 --> 00:46:53.994 line:90% position:50% align:center
for this period of Jehovah’s Kingdom work.”

00:46:56.330 --> 00:46:59.032 line:10% position:50% align:center
Brother Knorr helped to clarify the role

00:46:59.032 --> 00:47:01.401 line:10% position:50% align:center
of the Governing Body and its committees.

00:47:01.401 --> 00:47:03.403 line:10% position:50% align:center
Headquarters representatives

00:47:03.403 --> 00:47:06.039 line:10% position:50% align:center
were sent out to various branches,

00:47:06.039 --> 00:47:08.342 line:10% position:50% align:center
branches were better organized,

00:47:08.342 --> 00:47:10.711 line:10% position:50% align:center
bodies of elders were appointed

00:47:10.711 --> 00:47:12.980 line:10% position:50% align:center
in various congregations,

00:47:12.980 --> 00:47:15.549 line:10% position:50% align:center
training programs were instituted,

00:47:15.549 --> 00:47:17.584 line:10% position:50% align:center
and schools were established.

00:47:18.185 --> 00:47:19.686 line:10% position:50% align:center
Because of the organizational growth,

00:47:19.686 --> 00:47:21.421 line:10% position:50% align:center
the number of conventions

00:47:21.421 --> 00:47:22.923 line:10% position:50% align:center
being held worldwide

00:47:22.923 --> 00:47:25.058 line:10% position:50% align:center
now numbered into the hundreds,

00:47:25.058 --> 00:47:27.094 line:10% position:50% align:center
and the Governing Body members

00:47:27.094 --> 00:47:28.328 line:10% position:50% align:center
wanted to be present

00:47:28.328 --> 00:47:30.697 line:10% position:50% align:center
at as many of those conventions as possible.

00:47:31.164 --> 00:47:32.666 line:90% position:50% align:center
For example,

00:47:32.666 --> 00:47:35.502 line:90% position:50% align:center
at the 1969 “Peace on Earth”
International Convention,

00:47:35.502 --> 00:47:36.937 line:90% position:50% align:center
a Governing Body member

00:47:36.937 --> 00:47:38.772 line:90% position:50% align:center
would fly to the convention city

00:47:38.772 --> 00:47:40.274 line:90% position:50% align:center
for the opening day,

00:47:40.274 --> 00:47:43.510 line:90% position:50% align:center
catch a flight to another convention city,

00:47:43.510 --> 00:47:45.712 line:90% position:50% align:center
and then return to the original city

00:47:45.712 --> 00:47:48.215 line:90% position:50% align:center
so that he could speak on the closing day.

00:47:48.215 --> 00:47:50.551 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the 1970’s and 1980’s,

00:47:50.551 --> 00:47:52.052 line:90% position:50% align:center
many existing branches

00:47:52.052 --> 00:47:54.221 line:90% position:50% align:center
with printing and shipping capabilities

00:47:54.221 --> 00:47:56.523 line:90% position:50% align:center
needed to expand to ensure

00:47:56.523 --> 00:47:58.625 line:10% position:50% align:center
that the worldwide supply of spiritual food

00:47:58.625 --> 00:48:00.394 line:10% position:50% align:center
would flow uninterrupted

00:48:00.394 --> 00:48:03.030 line:90% position:50% align:center
no matter what happened on the world scene.

00:48:03.030 --> 00:48:04.264 line:90% position:50% align:center
At times,

00:48:04.264 --> 00:48:06.567 line:90% position:50% align:center
there were more than 20 branch construction

00:48:06.567 --> 00:48:08.135 line:90% position:50% align:center
or expansion projects

00:48:08.135 --> 00:48:09.736 line:90% position:50% align:center
going on simultaneously.

00:48:09.736 --> 00:48:10.871 line:10% position:50% align:center
And the Governing Body

00:48:10.871 --> 00:48:12.906 line:10% position:50% align:center
was very interested in each one

00:48:12.906 --> 00:48:14.274 line:10% position:50% align:center
and eager to dedicate

00:48:14.274 --> 00:48:16.810 line:10% position:50% align:center
the new facilities once completed.

00:48:18.412 --> 00:48:22.649 line:10% position:50% align:center
For me, it was always very encouraging

00:48:22.649 --> 00:48:26.253 line:90% position:50% align:center
to have contact
with the brothers of the Governing Body,

00:48:26.253 --> 00:48:28.655 line:90% position:50% align:center
to see their great zeal

00:48:28.655 --> 00:48:30.724 line:90% position:50% align:center
and their loving interests

00:48:30.724 --> 00:48:34.428 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the brothers behind the Iron Curtain.

00:48:34.428 --> 00:48:36.630 line:90% position:50% align:center
In 1977,

00:48:36.630 --> 00:48:39.733 line:90% position:50% align:center
something outstanding happened.

00:48:39.733 --> 00:48:42.402 line:90% position:50% align:center
In 1977,

00:48:42.402 --> 00:48:44.404 line:90% position:50% align:center
it was possible

00:48:44.404 --> 00:48:47.975 line:90% position:50% align:center
for Brothers Jaracz, Franz, and Sydlik

00:48:47.975 --> 00:48:50.811 line:90% position:50% align:center
to visit the brothers in Poland.

00:48:50.811 --> 00:48:53.146 line:90% position:50% align:center
So that was the first time

00:48:53.146 --> 00:48:55.148 line:90% position:50% align:center
—the first time—

00:48:55.148 --> 00:48:57.684 line:90% position:50% align:center
that members of the Governing Body

00:48:57.684 --> 00:48:59.686 line:90% position:50% align:center
could visit the country

00:48:59.686 --> 00:49:01.688 line:90% position:50% align:center
behind the Iron Curtain.

00:49:01.688 --> 00:49:04.257 line:90% position:50% align:center
They spoke to many overseers,

00:49:04.257 --> 00:49:07.828 line:90% position:50% align:center
pioneers, and longtime Witnesses.

00:49:07.828 --> 00:49:11.298 line:90% position:50% align:center
That was, of course, a wonderful experience.

00:49:11.298 --> 00:49:13.500 line:90% position:50% align:center
One year after this visit,

00:49:13.500 --> 00:49:15.669 line:90% position:50% align:center
Brother Jaracz along with Brother Henschel

00:49:15.669 --> 00:49:18.672 line:90% position:50% align:center
were able to get an appointment
with government officials

00:49:18.672 --> 00:49:23.176 line:90% position:50% align:center
to promote a more tolerant attitude
of Jehovah’s organization

00:49:23.176 --> 00:49:25.445 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the work
that Jehovah’s Witnesses were doing

00:49:25.445 --> 00:49:28.015 line:90% position:50% align:center
in Eastern Europe and especially in Poland.

00:49:28.015 --> 00:49:30.217 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now, mind you, this was all taking place

00:49:30.217 --> 00:49:32.519 line:90% position:50% align:center
some ten years prior

00:49:32.519 --> 00:49:35.355 line:90% position:50% align:center
to the fall of Communism in Eastern Europe.

00:49:36.056 --> 00:49:37.958 line:10% position:50% align:center
They took various steps

00:49:37.958 --> 00:49:40.027 line:10% position:50% align:center
to meet with the local brothers in person.

00:49:40.861 --> 00:49:42.696 line:90% position:50% align:center
And Brother Barry of the Governing Body

00:49:42.696 --> 00:49:45.065 line:90% position:50% align:center
had the opportunity to hold a secret meeting

00:49:45.065 --> 00:49:47.901 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the city of Leningrad with Brother Kose,

00:49:47.901 --> 00:49:50.537 line:90% position:50% align:center
who was responsible
for the activity in the territory.

00:49:50.537 --> 00:49:52.539 line:90% position:50% align:center
Brother Kose said that he received

00:49:52.539 --> 00:49:54.975 line:90% position:50% align:center
tremendous encouragement
from that discussion,

00:49:54.975 --> 00:49:57.210 line:90% position:50% align:center
from the conversation with Brother Barry.

00:49:58.679 --> 00:50:02.182 line:90% position:50% align:center
And it was interesting
that it wasn’t until after that meeting

00:50:02.182 --> 00:50:04.818 line:90% position:50% align:center
that Brother Kose found out
that he had been talking

00:50:04.818 --> 00:50:06.853 line:90% position:50% align:center
to a member of the Governing Body.

00:50:08.221 --> 00:50:09.322 line:10% position:50% align:center
The brothers in Eastern Europe

00:50:09.322 --> 00:50:11.191 line:10% position:50% align:center
really needed help to resist

00:50:11.191 --> 00:50:13.026 line:10% position:50% align:center
decades of satanic efforts

00:50:13.026 --> 00:50:15.095 line:90% position:50% align:center
to destroy their faith in Jehovah

00:50:15.095 --> 00:50:19.099 line:90% position:50% align:center
and weaken the unity
and confidence in His organization.

00:50:19.099 --> 00:50:21.868 line:90% position:50% align:center
The members of the Governing Body

00:50:21.868 --> 00:50:24.604 line:90% position:50% align:center
showed very deep appreciation

00:50:24.604 --> 00:50:26.606 line:10% position:50% align:center
for the brothers

00:50:26.606 --> 00:50:29.376 line:10% position:50% align:center
who kept the communication

00:50:29.376 --> 00:50:31.511 line:10% position:50% align:center
with the brothers behind the Iron Curtain.

00:50:31.511 --> 00:50:33.513 line:90% position:50% align:center
Because you have to imagine

00:50:33.513 --> 00:50:36.049 line:90% position:50% align:center
that to get the spiritual food there,

00:50:36.850 --> 00:50:40.921 line:90% position:50% align:center
they had to be willing
to take a personal risk

00:50:40.921 --> 00:50:42.923 line:90% position:50% align:center
to visit

00:50:42.923 --> 00:50:46.960 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to bring the spiritual food
to the brothers there,

00:50:46.960 --> 00:50:51.064 line:90% position:50% align:center
not just to the countries right close

00:50:51.064 --> 00:50:54.134 line:90% position:50% align:center
but down there to the brothers

00:50:54.134 --> 00:50:57.204 line:90% position:50% align:center
—down there to Siberia.

00:50:57.204 --> 00:51:00.040 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the second half of the 1980’s,

00:51:00.040 --> 00:51:02.476 line:90% position:50% align:center
the Iron Curtain began to open up.

00:51:03.944 --> 00:51:06.980 line:90% position:50% align:center
There was a sense of freedom in the air.

00:51:06.980 --> 00:51:11.084 line:90% position:50% align:center
The brothers in Eastern Europe
could feel that freedom.

00:51:11.084 --> 00:51:13.520 line:10% position:50% align:center
As governments granted permission,

00:51:13.520 --> 00:51:15.322 line:10% position:50% align:center
the Governing Body organized

00:51:15.322 --> 00:51:19.059 line:90% position:50% align:center
conventions in Eastern-bloc countries

00:51:19.059 --> 00:51:22.395 line:90% position:50% align:center
—for example, in Poland and Czechoslovakia.

00:51:23.163 --> 00:51:25.432 line:90% position:50% align:center
And when bans were lifted,

00:51:25.432 --> 00:51:27.667 line:90% position:50% align:center
the members of the Governing Body

00:51:27.667 --> 00:51:32.405 line:90% position:50% align:center
traveled many times
to all the countries that were possible

00:51:32.405 --> 00:51:34.407 line:90% position:50% align:center
—Poland, Hungary, Romania,

00:51:34.407 --> 00:51:36.877 line:90% position:50% align:center
Czechoslovakia, Russia, Ukraine,

00:51:36.877 --> 00:51:38.979 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to the Baltic States,

00:51:38.979 --> 00:51:42.149 line:90% position:50% align:center
and also to Belarus.

00:51:42.149 --> 00:51:44.184 line:90% position:50% align:center
In November 1989,

00:51:44.184 --> 00:51:46.186 line:90% position:50% align:center
the Berlin Wall came down.

00:51:46.186 --> 00:51:48.188 line:90% position:50% align:center
Well, this was a great turning point

00:51:48.188 --> 00:51:50.190 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the history of the 20th century.

00:51:50.190 --> 00:51:53.326 line:90% position:50% align:center
But it also meant greater freedom
for our brothers.

00:51:53.326 --> 00:51:55.796 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Governing Body really sprung into action.

00:51:55.796 --> 00:51:57.097 line:90% position:50% align:center
They wanted to go

00:51:57.097 --> 00:51:58.331 line:10% position:50% align:center
and accelerate the work there.

00:51:58.331 --> 00:52:00.333 line:10% position:50% align:center
So Brother Jaracz as well as other members

00:52:00.333 --> 00:52:01.368 line:10% position:50% align:center
of the Governing Body

00:52:01.368 --> 00:52:03.103 line:10% position:50% align:center
closely supervised the work.

00:52:03.103 --> 00:52:04.571 line:10% position:50% align:center
Therefore, the number of visits they made,

00:52:04.571 --> 00:52:06.573 line:10% position:50% align:center
well, just skyrocketed.

00:52:07.140 --> 00:52:09.209 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the fall of 1989,

00:52:09.209 --> 00:52:11.545 line:90% position:50% align:center
Brothers Milton Henschel and Theodore Jaracz

00:52:11.545 --> 00:52:13.680 line:90% position:50% align:center
had the unique opportunity of visiting

00:52:13.680 --> 00:52:15.782 line:90% position:50% align:center
the brothers in the Soviet Union

00:52:15.782 --> 00:52:17.784 line:90% position:50% align:center
for the first time.

00:52:17.784 --> 00:52:20.954 line:90% position:50% align:center
The brothers really wanted
to study the situation on the ground.

00:52:22.489 --> 00:52:26.159 line:90% position:50% align:center
They met with all of the elders,
circuit overseers,

00:52:26.159 --> 00:52:29.396 line:90% position:50% align:center
district overseers,
and members of the Country Committee.

00:52:30.630 --> 00:52:34.167 line:90% position:50% align:center
It was like one big shepherding visit.

00:52:36.369 --> 00:52:40.040 line:90% position:50% align:center
So in Eastern Europe,
1991 was the stage

00:52:40.040 --> 00:52:42.976 line:90% position:50% align:center
for three international conventions

00:52:42.976 --> 00:52:46.012 line:90% position:50% align:center
with the subject
“Lovers of Godly Freedom.”

00:52:46.012 --> 00:52:49.950 line:90% position:50% align:center
But, of course,
besides these international conventions,

00:52:49.950 --> 00:52:52.452 line:90% position:50% align:center
other open conventions

00:52:52.452 --> 00:52:56.423 line:90% position:50% align:center
(so not in secret, no, open conventions)

00:52:56.423 --> 00:52:58.892 line:90% position:50% align:center
were held for the first time

00:52:58.892 --> 00:53:01.127 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the former Soviet Union

00:53:01.127 --> 00:53:05.866 line:10% position:50% align:center
—in Estonia, in Russia, and in the Ukraine.

00:53:06.466 --> 00:53:08.468 line:90% position:50% align:center
Just imagine!

00:53:08.468 --> 00:53:11.571 line:90% position:50% align:center
After decades of such difficult persecution,

00:53:11.571 --> 00:53:14.174 line:90% position:50% align:center
we experienced the opportunity to be together

00:53:14.174 --> 00:53:16.409 line:90% position:50% align:center
with our worldwide brotherhood

00:53:16.409 --> 00:53:19.746 line:90% position:50% align:center
and to see the brothers
from the Governing Body.

00:53:19.746 --> 00:53:22.349 line:90% position:50% align:center
It was an unforgettable time.

00:53:22.349 --> 00:53:24.718 line:90% position:50% align:center
It was the happiest of times.

00:53:25.385 --> 00:53:27.554 line:90% position:50% align:center
It was super!

00:53:27.554 --> 00:53:32.425 line:90% position:50% align:center
One outstanding convention
was held in Zagreb.

00:53:32.425 --> 00:53:37.430 line:90% position:50% align:center
Yes, it was a loving
and a courageous decision

00:53:37.430 --> 00:53:40.667 line:90% position:50% align:center
of the Governing Body to go there

00:53:40.667 --> 00:53:43.737 line:90% position:50% align:center
despite the uncertainty

00:53:43.737 --> 00:53:47.140 line:90% position:50% align:center
of the political situation in the country

00:53:47.140 --> 00:53:51.444 line:90% position:50% align:center
and maybe (coming up) a civil war.

00:53:51.444 --> 00:53:55.615 line:90% position:50% align:center
This convention was the only public event

00:53:55.615 --> 00:53:58.551 line:90% position:50% align:center
that was allowed by the government

00:53:58.551 --> 00:53:59.619 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the city of Zagreb.

00:53:59.619 --> 00:54:02.455 line:90% position:50% align:center
All other public events

00:54:02.455 --> 00:54:04.124 line:90% position:50% align:center
were canceled,

00:54:04.124 --> 00:54:07.594 line:90% position:50% align:center
but the convention
of Jehovah’s Witnesses was not.

00:54:07.594 --> 00:54:09.663 line:90% position:50% align:center
Policemen and soldiers

00:54:09.663 --> 00:54:13.066 line:90% position:50% align:center
assigned to keep security
and order in the stadium

00:54:13.066 --> 00:54:16.670 line:90% position:50% align:center
were astonished that Serbians, Croats,

00:54:16.670 --> 00:54:19.973 line:90% position:50% align:center
Slovenians, Montenegrins, and Bosnians

00:54:19.973 --> 00:54:24.978 line:90% position:50% align:center
were sitting together in peace and in unity.

00:54:25.812 --> 00:54:28.248 line:10% position:50% align:center
At those international conventions

00:54:28.248 --> 00:54:29.516 line:10% position:50% align:center
in Eastern Europe,

00:54:29.516 --> 00:54:33.286 line:90% position:50% align:center
members of the Governing Body
gave the final motivating talk.

00:54:33.286 --> 00:54:36.823 line:90% position:50% align:center
And those talks,
given less than five months

00:54:36.823 --> 00:54:39.960 line:90% position:50% align:center
after the thrill
of obtaining legal recognition

00:54:39.960 --> 00:54:42.495 line:90% position:50% align:center
for our work in the Soviet Union,

00:54:42.495 --> 00:54:44.764 line:90% position:50% align:center
strengthened and encouraged our brothers

00:54:44.764 --> 00:54:47.367 line:90% position:50% align:center
for trials they would face in the future.

00:54:48.335 --> 00:54:51.304 line:90% position:50% align:center
It’s plain to see
that the Governing Body of years past

00:54:51.304 --> 00:54:52.906 line:90% position:50% align:center
expended themselves

00:54:52.906 --> 00:54:55.475 line:90% position:50% align:center
to “know well the appearance of [the] flock.”

00:54:55.475 --> 00:54:57.544 line:90% position:50% align:center
They poured themselves out

00:54:57.544 --> 00:54:58.845 line:90% position:50% align:center
“like a drink offering”

00:54:58.845 --> 00:55:01.715 line:90% position:50% align:center
in order to “take good care of [the] sheep.”

00:55:01.715 --> 00:55:03.717 line:90% position:50% align:center
The same deep love

00:55:03.717 --> 00:55:05.986 line:90% position:50% align:center
and tender concern for you,

00:55:05.986 --> 00:55:08.388 line:90% position:50% align:center
the sheep of the Great Shepherd’s flock,

00:55:08.388 --> 00:55:10.724 line:90% position:50% align:center
has been evident throughout modern times

00:55:10.724 --> 00:55:12.892 line:90% position:50% align:center
right down to this day.

00:55:14.627 --> 00:55:17.897 line:90% position:50% align:center
What striking evidence of unity

00:55:17.897 --> 00:55:21.201 line:90% position:50% align:center
our conventions provide! 

00:55:21.201 --> 00:55:24.671 line:90% position:50% align:center
While the world around them
roiled with ethnic strife,

00:55:24.671 --> 00:55:27.107 line:90% position:50% align:center
hatred, and violence,

00:55:27.107 --> 00:55:30.510 line:90% position:50% align:center
our brothers enjoyed a peaceful convention

00:55:30.510 --> 00:55:34.381 line:90% position:50% align:center
that rightly impressed the authorities.

00:55:34.381 --> 00:55:37.484 line:90% position:50% align:center
Our faith in the fine shepherd and his Father

00:55:37.484 --> 00:55:40.320 line:90% position:50% align:center
surely is being rewarded now

00:55:40.320 --> 00:55:45.191 line:90% position:50% align:center
and will be even more abundantly rewarded
in the future.

00:55:46.526 --> 00:55:51.097 line:90% position:50% align:center
Perhaps, like many,
you’re still talking about last year’s drama,

00:55:51.097 --> 00:55:54.834 line:90% position:50% align:center
<i>Daniel: A Lifetime of Faith.</i>

00:55:54.834 --> 00:55:58.638 line:90% position:50% align:center
What moving lessons
and awesome depictions

00:55:58.638 --> 00:56:02.042 line:90% position:50% align:center
of visions and events from his life!

00:56:02.042 --> 00:56:04.844 line:90% position:50% align:center
Would you like to take a look
behind the scenes

00:56:04.844 --> 00:56:07.247 line:90% position:50% align:center
and see what went into making it?

00:56:07.247 --> 00:56:10.450 line:90% position:50% align:center
Let’s enjoy a tour of some of the work

00:56:10.450 --> 00:56:14.220 line:90% position:50% align:center
that helped bring this account to life.

00:56:27.033 --> 00:56:29.102 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Bible book of Daniel

00:56:29.102 --> 00:56:31.638 line:90% position:50% align:center
is filled with imagery,

00:56:31.638 --> 00:56:33.006 line:90% position:50% align:center
visions,

00:56:34.407 --> 00:56:36.910 line:90% position:50% align:center
and amazing scenery and architecture.

00:56:39.112 --> 00:56:40.246 line:90% position:50% align:center
All of it serves

00:56:40.246 --> 00:56:43.450 line:90% position:50% align:center
to teach readers about the times we live in now

00:56:43.450 --> 00:56:46.553 line:90% position:50% align:center
and how we can faithfully serve Jehovah.

00:56:46.553 --> 00:56:48.154 line:90% position:50% align:center
The team that made 

00:56:48.154 --> 00:56:50.623 line:90% position:50% align:center
<i>Daniel: A Lifetime of Faith</i>

00:56:50.623 --> 00:56:54.194 line:90% position:50% align:center
had to portray these amazing things on film.

00:56:54.194 --> 00:56:56.196 line:90% position:50% align:center
How did they do it?

00:56:58.298 --> 00:57:00.133 line:90% position:50% align:center
Early concept art

00:57:00.133 --> 00:57:02.535 line:90% position:50% align:center
was made to help in the development

00:57:02.535 --> 00:57:05.271 line:90% position:50% align:center
of the many visual effects scenes.

00:57:16.015 --> 00:57:18.952 line:90% position:50% align:center
The architecture and aesthetics of Babylon

00:57:18.952 --> 00:57:20.653 line:90% position:50% align:center
were quite different

00:57:20.653 --> 00:57:22.422 line:90% position:50% align:center
from what the Israelites were used to.

00:57:23.957 --> 00:57:26.359 line:90% position:50% align:center
The sets needed to be designed in a way

00:57:26.359 --> 00:57:29.529 line:90% position:50% align:center
that helped convey
what it was like to be captured

00:57:33.933 --> 00:57:35.835 line:90% position:50% align:center
and brought to a foreign land.

00:57:39.272 --> 00:57:41.875 line:90% position:50% align:center
The production design and sets

00:57:41.875 --> 00:57:46.012 line:90% position:50% align:center
and props departments built 360-degree sets,

00:57:46.012 --> 00:57:49.983 line:90% position:50% align:center
which made for an immersive environment.

00:57:54.320 --> 00:57:58.491 line:90% position:50% align:center
All of the other wise men are unable to make
the interpretation known to me.

00:57:59.893 --> 00:58:01.895 line:90% position:50% align:center
But you are able to do so.

00:58:12.739 --> 00:58:15.508 line:90% position:50% align:center
Many costumes and props

00:58:15.508 --> 00:58:17.377 line:90% position:50% align:center
were carefully handmade for the production.

00:58:22.215 --> 00:58:24.884 line:90% position:50% align:center
Spearheads were hand-forged.

00:58:28.721 --> 00:58:30.423 line:90% position:50% align:center
Most of the filming was done

00:58:30.423 --> 00:58:33.693 line:90% position:50% align:center
at Mount Ebo Studios in Brewster, New York.

00:58:39.666 --> 00:58:42.101 line:90% position:50% align:center
Some additional scenes
were filmed in nearby locations

00:58:45.705 --> 00:58:47.040 line:90% position:50% align:center
and in Florida.

00:58:49.042 --> 00:58:50.543 line:90% position:50% align:center
You need to rest.

00:58:55.615 --> 00:58:57.951 line:90% position:50% align:center
Several miniature sets were built,

00:58:57.951 --> 00:58:59.419 line:90% position:50% align:center
including a ziggurat,

00:59:03.723 --> 00:59:06.593 line:90% position:50% align:center
and then actors were filmed
in front of a green screen

00:59:06.593 --> 00:59:09.429 line:90% position:50% align:center
and inserted into the final shots.

00:59:12.765 --> 00:59:16.035 line:90% position:50% align:center
As filming was completed,
scenes were edited together

00:59:17.403 --> 00:59:18.905 line:90% position:50% align:center
and the visual-effects team

00:59:18.905 --> 00:59:21.874 line:90% position:50% align:center
went to work on many specialized shots.

00:59:28.147 --> 00:59:31.251 line:90% position:50% align:center
Digital models of people and animals

00:59:31.251 --> 00:59:32.619 line:90% position:50% align:center
were animated and combined

00:59:32.619 --> 00:59:34.487 line:90% position:50% align:center
with footage of real environments

00:59:34.487 --> 00:59:36.122 line:90% position:50% align:center
to make scenes

00:59:36.122 --> 00:59:38.925 line:90% position:50% align:center
that would have been impossible to film otherwise.

00:59:39.926 --> 00:59:41.427 line:90% position:50% align:center
For example,

00:59:41.427 --> 00:59:43.963 line:90% position:50% align:center
a digital model was made of the immense image

00:59:43.963 --> 00:59:46.432 line:90% position:50% align:center
in King Nebuchadnezzar’s dream.

00:59:47.433 --> 00:59:49.769 line:90% position:50% align:center
The team researched the characteristics

00:59:49.769 --> 00:59:52.105 line:90% position:50% align:center
of the actual materials described
in the Scriptures,

00:59:52.972 --> 00:59:56.576 line:90% position:50% align:center
such as metals and rocks,

00:59:56.576 --> 00:59:58.511 line:90% position:50% align:center
so that when the image falls,

00:59:58.511 --> 01:00:01.314 line:90% position:50% align:center
it appears realistic and believable.

01:00:16.629 --> 01:00:19.899 line:90% position:50% align:center
Just look at the results of thousands of hours

01:00:19.899 --> 01:00:22.201 line:90% position:50% align:center
spent modeling,

01:00:22.201 --> 01:00:25.204 line:90% position:50% align:center
animating, simulating,

01:00:25.204 --> 01:00:28.474 line:90% position:50% align:center
rendering, and compositing!

01:00:44.691 --> 01:00:48.494 line:90% position:50% align:center
Music and sound effects add the final touches.

01:01:01.307 --> 01:01:02.775 line:90% position:50% align:center
“What do you see?”

01:01:03.543 --> 01:01:05.912 line:90% position:50% align:center
Jehovah asked the prophet Amos.

01:01:08.381 --> 01:01:11.718 line:90% position:50% align:center
What Amos saw taught him important lessons.

01:01:15.088 --> 01:01:18.691 line:90% position:50% align:center
In the drama <i>Daniel: A Lifetime of Faith,</i>

01:01:19.492 --> 01:01:21.194 line:90% position:50% align:center
what did you see?

01:01:24.731 --> 01:01:28.434 line:90% position:50% align:center
And more important, what did you learn?

01:01:32.839 --> 01:01:34.907 line:90% position:50% align:center
What did you see?

01:01:34.907 --> 01:01:37.377 line:90% position:50% align:center
Hours of hard work?

01:01:37.377 --> 01:01:40.380 line:90% position:50% align:center
Dramatic visual effects?

01:01:40.380 --> 01:01:44.417 line:90% position:50% align:center
Bible characters brought to life on-screen?

01:01:44.417 --> 01:01:48.020 line:90% position:50% align:center
Isn’t it amazing how they all combine

01:01:48.020 --> 01:01:50.857 line:90% position:50% align:center
to make what happened
thousands of years ago

01:01:50.857 --> 01:01:55.194 line:90% position:50% align:center
seem so real, so vivid,
and so faith-strengthening?

01:01:56.329 --> 01:02:00.133 line:90% position:50% align:center
Now let’s enjoy this month’s postcard

01:02:00.133 --> 01:02:04.904 line:90% position:50% align:center
as together we climb
the peaks of Switzerland.

01:02:05.838 --> 01:02:09.075 line:90% position:50% align:center
About 70 percent of Switzerland

01:02:09.075 --> 01:02:11.210 line:90% position:50% align:center
is covered by mountains.

01:02:11.210 --> 01:02:17.116 line:90% position:50% align:center
Its tallest mountain rises to 4,634 meters,

01:02:17.116 --> 01:02:21.888 line:90% position:50% align:center
or over 15,000 feet, above sea level.

01:02:21.888 --> 01:02:26.826 line:90% position:50% align:center
Switzerland has
four official languages: German,

01:02:26.826 --> 01:02:30.530 line:90% position:50% align:center
French, Italian, and Romansh,

01:02:31.230 --> 01:02:35.635 line:90% position:50% align:center
a descendant language of the Latin
spoken in the Roman Empire.

01:02:35.635 --> 01:02:38.838 line:90% position:50% align:center
Switzerland has beautiful waterfalls,

01:02:38.838 --> 01:02:41.474 line:90% position:50% align:center
glaciers, lakes,

01:02:41.474 --> 01:02:43.910 line:90% position:50% align:center
rivers, streams,

01:02:43.910 --> 01:02:46.412 line:90% position:50% align:center
and alpine meadows.

01:02:46.412 --> 01:02:48.981 line:90% position:50% align:center
Cows graze these meadows,

01:02:48.981 --> 01:02:52.018 line:90% position:50% align:center
and from their milk, the Swiss make

01:02:52.018 --> 01:02:56.756 line:90% position:50% align:center
about 450 varieties of delicious cheese.

01:02:57.256 --> 01:03:00.259 line:90% position:50% align:center
Switzerland is also well-known

01:03:00.259 --> 01:03:02.762 line:90% position:50% align:center
for another treat: chocolate.

01:03:02.762 --> 01:03:06.199 line:90% position:50% align:center
In fact, the Swiss consume
more chocolate per person

01:03:06.199 --> 01:03:09.302 line:90% position:50% align:center
than people in any other country
in the world!

01:03:10.169 --> 01:03:14.540 line:90% position:50% align:center
Since Switzerland didn’t participate
in World War I,

01:03:14.540 --> 01:03:18.678 line:90% position:50% align:center
it provided an ideal location to establish

01:03:18.678 --> 01:03:22.615 line:90% position:50% align:center
the first Central European branch office
of Jehovah’s Witnesses

01:03:22.615 --> 01:03:25.651 line:90% position:50% align:center
in the early 1920’s.

01:03:25.651 --> 01:03:29.856 line:90% position:50% align:center
During World War II,
Jehovah’s Witnesses from Switzerland

01:03:30.623 --> 01:03:34.193 line:90% position:50% align:center
helped to provide waters of truth
to other countries in Europe.

01:03:34.827 --> 01:03:38.965 line:90% position:50% align:center
At great effort and cost,
our brothers found ways

01:03:38.965 --> 01:03:42.969 line:90% position:50% align:center
to get spiritual food
to their brothers in Nazi Germany.

01:03:43.803 --> 01:03:48.274 line:90% position:50% align:center
After World War II,
our Swiss brothers generously donated

01:03:48.274 --> 01:03:52.245 line:90% position:50% align:center
food, clothing, and money
to support the brotherhood

01:03:52.245 --> 01:03:55.982 line:90% position:50% align:center
as part of the first
large-scale relief effort

01:03:55.982 --> 01:03:58.584 line:90% position:50% align:center
of our modern-day organization.

01:03:59.652 --> 01:04:03.823 line:90% position:50% align:center
Today, over 19,000 Witnesses
across the country

01:04:03.823 --> 01:04:06.993 line:90% position:50% align:center
meet in 264 congregations

01:04:06.993 --> 01:04:08.861 line:90% position:50% align:center
as well as in 39 groups

01:04:08.861 --> 01:04:11.864 line:90% position:50% align:center
or pregroups in 26 languages.

01:04:12.632 --> 01:04:16.369 line:90% position:50% align:center
Even though a small percentage
of the population speaks Romansh,

01:04:16.369 --> 01:04:20.706 line:90% position:50% align:center
our fellow Witnesses make a concerted effort

01:04:20.706 --> 01:04:24.510 line:90% position:50% align:center
to reach them in the language of their heart.

01:04:24.510 --> 01:04:29.181 line:90% position:50% align:center
The 53 publishers in the Bever Congregation

01:04:29.181 --> 01:04:32.952 line:90% position:50% align:center
are busy spreading Kingdom truth.

01:04:32.952 --> 01:04:36.956 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Kingdom Hall in Bever
is located in the middle of the Alps

01:04:36.956 --> 01:04:41.494 line:90% position:50% align:center
at a height of some 1,700 meters,
or 5,500 feet,

01:04:41.494 --> 01:04:44.230 line:90% position:50% align:center
making it one of the highest Kingdom Halls

01:04:44.230 --> 01:04:46.899 line:90% position:50% align:center
in all of Europe.

01:04:46.899 --> 01:04:50.069 line:90% position:50% align:center
The congregation has 10 regular pioneers

01:04:50.069 --> 01:04:52.438 line:90% position:50% align:center
and also hosts an Italian group

01:04:52.438 --> 01:04:55.374 line:90% position:50% align:center
supported by 15 publishers.

01:04:55.374 --> 01:05:00.313 line:90% position:50% align:center
The Bever Congregation sends its warm love

01:05:00.313 --> 01:05:03.316 line:90% position:50% align:center
to our worldwide family.

01:05:04.350 --> 01:05:08.354 line:90% position:50% align:center
From the World Headquarters
of Jehovah’s Witnesses,

01:05:08.354 --> 01:05:12.191 line:90% position:50% align:center
this is JW Broadcasting.

